### Concl;usion

Whatever your investment decision is, make an informed one. Know why you‚Äôre buying this asset rather than another.. Keep learning and regularly check if your thesis is still intact. Don‚Äôt be in denial if you are wrong.

Understand the risk of losing money. . 

Be aware of how much tax you‚Äôll have to pay in the end. Familiarize yourself with tax-deferred accounts like IRAs and 401(k)s. Understand the withdrawal rules for them and learn if they would benefit you.

be as tax-efficient as possible. For example, in the US, municipal bond funds and municipal bond-based money market funds are exempt from state tax.

Everyone makes mistakes in their investment journey; make sure they won‚Äôt hurt you for the rest of your life.

You will always hear success stories of someone earning 1000x their money in options, Bitcoin, or Nvidia. Remember, only those who made money show off. The 90% who made similar bets and lost don‚Äôt share their stories. You only hear from the winners. Be responsible with money

Please don‚Äôt YOLO your money.

With everything digital, you might not even realize the gravity of the situation when you‚Äôre risking a big chunk of your net worth. The severity of the situation will only hit you after all the money is lost.
